5:
Wow... Everyone here's covered with
fur, just like Nimbus.
12:
Heh-heh, indeed. What an
interesting world!
16:
But there are lost items to be found
in this world, as wellâ€”
22:
...I'm all right. It all just hit me a little
suddenly...
29:
Yes, this place received some of the
worst of the fighting... But perhaps
you know this already?
33:
I do. A great deal of regret fills the air
in this place. Such restless energy...
41:
Are you looking for someone,
Hildegarde?
45:
I mentioned earlier that I've only
ever met one other person who
could hear the same voices as I.
48:
That person was my mentor... My
mentor taught me how to use my
abilities, and was previously the
head of the Memento Recovery
Guild.
50:
One day, my mentor's memento got
caught up in a shift in the
Kaleidoscope, and I haven't seen it
since.
53:
Don't tell Falsche, now! I feel that I'd
be embarrassed, somehow.
67:
Yes, I do. Would you accompany me
for a bit? Oh, and also...
73:
Good afternoon, you three. Sorry to
trouble you, but I need you to return
that ring you've got in your pocket.
76:
You killed the ring's owner and took
it for yourself, yes?
79:
My, it's not just the ring, is it?
Everything you three are wearing
was taken off your victims.
82:
You simply radiate an aura of the
dead's lamentations. What a
miserable state of affairs...
85:
Y-you can't just walk in here and
make crazy accusations like that,
lady! I bought this at a pawnshop,
soâ€”
90:
You can't, can you? Because you're
a bunch of greasy thieves.
95:
In that case, we hope you'll
accompany us for a moment.
98:
We just want to ask some questions.
If you're innocent, it'll all be over
quickly.
105:
What a shame... To think that all of
these items were stolen...
107:
I'd like to return everything to the
victims' surviving relatives... But I am
not certain we'll have much success
tracking down so many families.
111:
Oh... Don't worry about that. That's
where Hildegarde shines.
115:
Sorry to trouble you, but could I ask
for your assistance?
120:
Of course. As head of the Memento
Recovery Guild, I'll return every item
that I possibly can to the bereaved.
123:
...However, would it be all right for
me to hold onto the items for which I
cannot find a home?
130:
So now all you've got to do is go
return these things, right?
143:
Sorry... I'm just not used to people
helping me like this. It's strange.
146:
...I can say the same for Falsche,
but... You're an odd bunch, aren't
you?
150:
...You're the last person I wanna hear
that from. Besides, it's not like it's just
us, you know.
154:
Yes. The people at your guild want
to help you, too.
169:
I see. I'm not so sure... It's difficult for
me to see such pure qualities in the
living.
173: But, if that's true... I'd be delighted.
183:
...Haha, it's good to see you,
everyone!
186:
...Everyone's here, yes? Please,
gather here for a moment.
190:
Ta-da! I found some lovely
chocolates out on my trip, so I
bought a box for everybody to enjoy
together.
195:
That's right. I wanted to let you know
just how much you all mean to me.
202:
They look. Delicious. Thank you.
Hildegarde.
205:
Y-yeah. Thank you very much! I was
just a little taken aback for a
second, but I really appreciate it!
211: ...Now then, I hope you enjoy them.
218: You should. Eat with us. Hildegarde...
221:
Yes! Let's have a little party! I'll go
prepare some tea!
228:
All right, then... Let's all have a
splendid time together.
